ommit (required for branch operations)\\necho \\\"# Test Repo\\\" > README.md\\ngit add README.md\\ngit commit -m \\\"Initial commit\\\"\\n```\\n\\n### Step 3: Create the .factory/ Directory\\n\\nThe Droid agent detects Entire via a `.factory/` directory. Create it in your test repo:\\n\\n```bash\\nmkdir -p .factory\\n```\\n\\n### Step 4: Build the Entire Binary\\n\\nFrom the CLI repository, build the binary directly into your test repo:\\n\\n```bash\\ncd /Users/alisha/Projects/devenv/cli\\n\\n# Build the binary\\ngo build -o /tmp/droid-test/entire ./cmd/entire\\n```\\n\\nVerify the binary works:\\n\\n```bash\\ncd /tmp/droid-test\\n./entire --version\\n```\\n\\n### Step 5: Install Hooks\\n\\nIn your test repo, run the `enable` command to install hooks and configure `.factory/settings.json`:\\n\\n```bash\\ncd /tmp/droid-test\\n./entire enable\\n```\\n\\nThis command:\\n- Installs git hooks (prepare-commit-msg, post-commit, pre-push)\\n- Creates `.factory/settings.json` with Entire configuration\\n- Sets up `.entire/logs/` directory\\n\\nVerify the configuration:\\n\\n```bash\\ncat .factory/settings.json\\n```\\n\\n## Running Droid with Local Hooks\\n\\nThis is the critical part. Git hooks invoke `entire` by name (not by absolute path), so they rely on PATH resolution. By default, the system-installed Entire (e.g., `/opt/homebrew/bin/entire`) may be older and won't work correctly with Droid.\\n\\n### Step 1: Prepend Test Repo to PATH\\n\\nBefore launching Droid, ensure your local binary takes precedence:\\n\\n```bash\\ncd /tmp/droid-test\\nexport PATH=\\\"$(pwd):$PATH\\\"\\n```\\n\\nVerify the local binary is found:\\n\\n```bash\\nwhich entire\\n# Should output: /tmp/droid-test/entire\\n```\\n\\n### Step 2: Launch Droid\\n\\n```bash\\ndroid\\n```\\n\\nDroid will detect the `.factory/` directory and begin interacting with Entire through git hooks.\\n\\n## What to Test\\n\\nVerify the following during a Droid session:\\n\\n### Hook Installation\\n\\n```bash\\n# Check that hooks are present\\nls -la .git/hooks/ | grep -E \\\"prepare-commit-msg|post-commit|pre-push\\\"\\n\\n# Verify settings\\ncat .factory/settings.json\\n```\\n\\n### Session Lifecycle\\n\\nAs Droid works, watch for these events in the logs:\\n\\n- **session-start** - New session begins (when Droid starts)\\n- **user-prompt-submit** - Droid submits a prompt\\n- **stop** - Droid stops working on a turn\\n- **session-end** - Session ends (when Droid finishes)\\n\\n### Checkpoints\\n\\nAfter a Droid turn, verify checkpoints were saved:\\n\\n```bash\\n# List checkpoints\\n./entire log\\n\\n# Sample output shows checkpoint IDs, timestamps, and file counts\\n```\\n\\n### Shadow Branches\\n\\nCheck for shadow branches created during the session:\\n\\n```bash\\ngit branch | grep entire/\\n# Should see branches like: entire/<commit-hash>-<worktree-hash>\\n```\\n\\n### Rewind Functionality\\n\\nIf testing rewind, verify you can restore from a checkpoint:\\n\\n```bash\\n# List available rewind points\\n./entire rewind\\n\\n# Rewind to a specific checkpoint (if fully rewinding is supported)\\n./entire rewind <checkpoint-id>\\n```\\n\\n### Commit Condensation\\n\\nWhen Droid makes a commit, verify it includes the Entire-Checkpoint trailer:\\n\\n```bash\\ngit log -1 --format=%B\\n# Should contain: Entire-Checkpoint: <12-hex-char-id>\\n```\\n\\n### Logs\\n\\nAll operations are logged to `.entire/logs/entire.log`. Check for errors or unexpected behavior:\\n\\n```bash\\ncat .entire/logs/entire.log | jq .\\n```\\n\\n## Verifying Hooks Fire\\n\\nWatch hooks execute in real-time using the logs:\\n\\n```bash\\n# Terminal 1: Tail the log with JSON pretty-printing\\ncd /tmp/droid-test\\ntail -f .entire/logs/entire.log | jq .\\n\\n# Terminal 2: Run Droid or make commits\\ndroid\\n# OR\\ncd /tmp/droid-test && git commit -m \\\"test\\\"\\n```\\n\\nFilter logs for Droid-specific activity:\\n\\n```bash\\njq 'select(.msg | test(\\\"factoryai|droid\\\"; \\\"i\\\"))' .entire/logs/entire.log\\n```