equired for branch operations)\\n    35→echo \\\"# Test Repo\\\" > README.md\\n    36→git add README.md\\n    37→git commit -m \\\"Initial commit\\\"\\n    38→```\\n    39→\\n    40→### Step 3: Create the .factory/ Directory\\n    41→\\n    42→The Droid agent detects Entire via a `.factory/` directory. Create it in your test repo:\\n    43→\\n    44→```bash\\n    45→mkdir -p .factory\\n    46→```\\n    47→\\n    48→### Step 4: Build the Entire Binary\\n    49→\\n    50→From the CLI repository, build the binary directly into your test repo:\\n    51→\\n    52→```bash\\n    53→cd /Users/alisha/Projects/devenv/cli\\n    54→\\n    55→# Build the binary\\n    56→go build -o /tmp/droid-test/entire ./cmd/entire\\n    57→```\\n    58→\\n    59→Verify the binary works:\\n    60→\\n    61→```bash\\n    62→cd /tmp/droid-test\\n    63→./entire --version\\n    64→```\\n    65→\\n    66→### Step 5: Install Hooks\\n    67→\\n    68→In your test repo, run the `enable` command to install hooks and configure `.factory/settings.json`:\\n    69→\\n    70→```bash\\n    71→cd /tmp/droid-test\\n    72→./entire enable\\n    73→```\\n    74→\\n    75→This command:\\n    76→- Installs git hooks (prepare-commit-msg, post-commit, pre-push)\\n    77→- Creates `.factory/settings.json` with Entire configuration\\n    78→- Sets up `.entire/logs/` directory\\n    79→\\n    80→Verify the configuration:\\n    81→\\n    82→```bash\\n    83→cat .factory/settings.json\\n    84→```\\n    85→\\n    86→## Running Droid with Local Hooks\\n    87→\\n    88→This is the critical part. Git hooks invoke `entire` by name (not by absolute path), so they rely on PATH resolution. By default, the system-installed Entire (e.g., `/opt/homebrew/bin/entire`) may be older and won't work correctly with Droid.\\n    89→\\n    90→### Step 1: Prepend Test Repo to PATH\\n    91→\\n    92→Before launching Droid, ensure your local binary takes precedence:\\n    93→\\n    94→```bash\\n    95→cd /tmp/droid-test\\n    96→export PATH=\\\"$(pwd):$PATH\\\"\\n    97→```\\n    98→\\n    99→Verify the local binary is found:\\n   100→\\n   101→```bash\\n   102→which entire\\n   103→# Should output: /tmp/droid-test/entire\\n   104→```\\n   105→\\n   106→### Step 2: Launch Droid\\n   107→\\n   108→```bash\\n   109→droid\\n   110→```\\n   111→\\n   112→Droid will detect the `.factory/` directory and begin interacting with Entire through git hooks.\\n   113→\\n   114→## What to Test\\n   115→\\n   116→Verify the following during a Droid session:\\n   117→\\n   118→### Hook Installation\\n   119→\\n   120→```bash\\n   121→# Check that hooks are present\\n   122→ls -la .git/hooks/ | grep -E \\\"prepare-commit-msg|post-commit|pre-push\\\"\\n   123→\\n   124→# Verify settings\\n   125→cat .factory/settings.json\\n   126→```\\n   127→\\n   128→### Session Lifecycle\\n   129→\\n   130→As Droid works, watch for these events in the logs:\\n   131→\\n   132→- **session-start** - New session begins (when Droid starts)\\n   133→- **user-prompt-submit** - Droid submits a prompt\\n   134→- **stop** - Droid stops working on a turn\\n   135→- **session-end** - Session ends (when Droid finishes)\\n   136→\\n   137→### Checkpoints\\n   138→\\n   139→After a Droid turn, verify checkpoints were saved:\\n   140→\\n   141→```bash\\n   142→# List checkpoints\\n   143→./entire log\\n   144→\\n   145→# Sample output shows checkpoint IDs, timestamps, and file counts\\n   146→```\\n   147→\\n   148→### Shadow Branches\\n   149→\\n   150→Check for shadow branches created during the session:\\n   151→\\n   152→```bash\\n   153→git branch | grep entire/\\n   154→# Should see branches like: entire/<commit-hash>-<worktree-hash>\\n   155→```\\n   156→\\n   157→### Rewind Functionality\\n   158→\\n   159→If testing rewind, verify you can restore from a checkpoint:\\n   160→\\n   161→```bash\\n   162→# List available rewind points\\n   163→./entire rewind\\n   164→\\n   165→# Rewind to a specific checkpoint (if fully rewinding is supported)\\n   166→./entire rewind <checkpoint-id>\\n   167→```\\n   168→\\n   169→### Commit Condensation\\n   170→\\n   171→When Droid makes a commit, verify it includes the Entire-Checkpoint trailer:\\n   172→\\n   173→```bash\\n   174→git log -1 --format=%B\\n   175→# Should contain: Entire-Checkpoint: <12-hex-char-id>\\n   176→```\\n   177→\\n   178→### Logs\\n   179→\\n   180→All operations are logged to `.entire/logs/entire.log`. Check for errors or unexpected behavior:\\n   181→\\n   182→```bash\\n   183→cat .entire/logs/entire.log | jq .\\n   184→```\\n   185→\\n   186→## Verifying Hooks Fire\\n   187→\\n   188→Watch hooks execute in real-time using the logs:\\n   189→\\n   190→```bash\\n   191→# Terminal 1: Tail the log with JSON pretty-printing\\n   192→cd /tmp/droid-test\\n   193→tail -f .entire/logs/entire.log | jq .\\n   194→\\n   195→# Terminal 2: Run Droid or make commits\\n   196→droid\\n   197→# OR\\n   198→cd /tmp/droid-test && git commit -m \\\"test\\\"\\n   199→```\\n   200→\\n   201→Filter logs for Droid-specific activity:\\n   202→\\n   203→```bash\\n   204→jq 'select(.msg | test(\\\"factoryai|droid\\\"; \\\"i\\\"))' .entire/logs/entire.log\\n   205→```\\n   206→\\n   207→## Troubleshooting\\n   208→\\n   209→### \\\"Commands called by hooks\\\" Message Appears\\n   210→\\n   211→This help text indicates the wrong binary is being invoked. The system-installed Entire is handling the hook call instead of your local binary.\\n   212→\\n   213→**Solution:**\\n   214→\\n   215→```bash\\n   216→# Verify PATH is set correctly\\n   217→echo $PATH\\n   218→which entire  # Should show your test repo path, not /opt/homebrew/bin/entire\\n   219→\\n   220→# Re-export PATH if needed\\n   221→export PATH=\\\"/tmp/droid-test:$PATH\\\"\\n   222→```\\n   223→\\n   224→### No Logs Appearing\\n   225→\\n   226→If `.entire/logs/entire.log` is empty or missing, hooks aren't reaching the handler.\\n   227→\\n   228→**Debugging steps:**\\n   229→\\n   230→1. Verify the hooks are executable:\\n   231→   ```bash\\n   232→   ls -la .git/hooks/prepare-commit-msg\\n   233→   chmod +x .git/hooks/prepare-commit-msg\\n   234→   ```\\n   235→\\n   236→2. Test hook execution manually:\\n   237→   ```bash\\n   238→   .git/hooks/prepare-commit-msg /tmp/test-msg\\n   239→   ```\\n   240→\\n   241→3. Check `which entire` resolves to your local binary.\\n   242→\\n   243→### Build Changes Not Reflected\\n   244→\\n   245→If you modify the CLI code and run Droid with the old binary, you won't see your changes.\\n   246→\\n   247→**Solution:**\\n   248→\\n   249→Rebuild the binary after each code change:\\n   250→\\n   251→```bash\\n   252→cd /Users/alisha/Projects/devenv/cli\\n   253→go build -o /tmp/droid-test/entire ./cmd/entire\\n   254→\\n   255→# Then in test repo, kill Droid and restart\\n   256→```\\n   257→\\n   258→## Alternative: Local-Dev Mode\\n   259→\\n   260→If you're iterating on code and don't want to rebuild the binary repeatedly, use local-dev mode. This uses `go run` to compile and execute on-the-fly (slower due to compilation, but no rebuild needed).\\n   261→\\n   262→### Setup\\n   263→\\n   264→From your test repo:\\n   265→\\n   266→```bash\\n   267→cd /tmp/droid-test\\n   268→\\n   269→# Set the path to the CLI repository\\n   270→REDACTED ./entire enable --local-dev\\n   271→```\\n   272→\\n   273→This configures Entire to use `go run` instead of a binary, reading code directly from the CLI repository.\\n   274→\\n   275→### Running Droid with Local-Dev\\n   276→\\n   277→```bash\\n   278→cd /tmp/droid-test\\n   279→export PATH=\\\"$(pwd):$PATH\\\"\\n   280→\\n   281→# Also set the factory project directory for hook execution\\n   282→export REDACTED\\n   283→\\n   284→droid\\n   285→```\\n   286→\\n   287→Each hook invocation will compile and run the latest code. This is slower but useful during rapid iteration.\\n   288→\\n   289→### Switching Back to Binary Mode\\n   290→\\n   291→To revert to binary mode:\\n   292→\\n   293→```bash\\n   294→cd /tmp/droid-test\\n   295→\\n   296→# Rebuild the binary\\n   297→go build -o /tmp/droid-test/entire /Users/alisha/Projects/devenv/cli/cmd/entire\\n   298→\\n   299→# Re-enable without --local-dev\\n   300→./entire enable\\n   301→```\\n   302→\\n   303→## Cleanup\\n   304→\\n   305→When testing is complete, remove the test repository:\\n   306→\\n   307→```bash\\n   308→rm -rf /tmp/droid-test\\n   309→# OR\\n   310→rm -rf ~/Projects/test-repos/factoryai-droid\\n   311→```\\n   312→\\n   313→This frees up disk space and ensures a clean slate for future tests.\\n   314→\\n   315→## Additional Notes\\n   316→\\n   317→### Session State Management\\n   318→\\n   319→Sessions are tracked in `.git/entire-sessions/`. Each active session has a JSON file containing:\\n   320→- Base commit\\n   321→- Checkpoint count\\n   322→- Session phase (ACTIVE, IDLE, ENDED)\\n   323→\\n   324→You can inspect session state for debugging:\\n   325→\\n   326→```bash\\n   327→cat .git/entire-sessions/*.json | jq .\\n   328→```\\n   329→\\n   330→### Multi-Session Testing\\n   331→\\n   332→If you want to test multiple concurrent Droid sessions in different worktrees, each worktree gets its own shadow branch namespace (worktree-hash is included in the branch name), so they won't conflict.\\n   333→\\n   334→```bash\\n   335→# In separate worktrees\\n   336→git worktree add ../test-repo-2\\n   337→\\n   338→# Each worktree can run Droid independently\\n   339→# Shadow branches will be separate: entire/<hash>-<worktree1> and entire/<hash>-<worktree2>\\n   340→```\\n   341→\\n   342→### Git Worktree Considerations\\n   343→\\n   344→The manual-commit strategy (default) is worktree-aware. Shadow branches include a worktree hash to prevent conflicts when using git worktrees. This allows safe, concurrent Droid sessions across different worktrees in the same repository.\\n   345→\"}]},\"uuid\":\"01419cb1-416b-4fd0-8cc5-0fa55428236f\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-02-19T19:37:19.398Z\",\"toolUseResult\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"file\":{\"filePath\":\"/Users/alisha/Projects/devenv/cli/test-files/manual-testing-factoryai-droid.md\",\"content\":\"# Manual Testing Guide: Factory AI Droid Agent Integration\\n\\nThis guide walks through manually testing the Factory AI Droid agent integration with the Entire CLI locally.\\n\\n## Prerequisites\\n\\n- Factory AI Droid (`droid` CLI) installed and in PATH\\n- Go toolchain (1.25.x or later)\\n- Git installed\\n- A shell environment (bash/zsh)\\n\\n## Setup\\n\\n### Step 1: Create a Test Repository\\n\\nCreate a new test repository outside the CLI project. This keeps your testing isolated from the main codebase.\\n\\n```bash\\n# Example locations\\nmkdir -p /tmp/droid-test\\n# OR\\nmkdir -p ~/Projects/test-repos/factoryai-droid\\n\\ncd /tmp/droid-test\\n```\\n\\n### Step 2: Initialize Git\\n\\n```bash\\ngit init\\ngit config user.email \\\"test@example.com\\\"\\ngit config user.name \\\"Test User\\\"\\n\\n# Create an initial commit (required for branch operations)\\necho \\\"# Test Repo\\\" > README.md\\ngit add README.md\\ngit commit -m \\\"Initial commit\\\"\\n```\\n\\n### Step 3: Create the .factory/ Directory\\n\\nThe Droid agent detects Entire via a `.factory/` directory. Create it in your test repo:\\n\\n```bash\\nmkdir -p .factory\\n```\\n\\n### Step 4: Build the Entire Binary\\n\\nFrom the CLI repository, build the binary directly into your test repo:\\n\\n```bash\\ncd /Users/alisha/Projects/devenv/cli\\n\\n# Build the binary\\ngo build -o /tmp/droid-test/entire ./cmd/entire\\n```\\n\\nVerify the binary works:\\n\\n```bash\\ncd /tmp/droid-test\\n./entire --version\\n```\\n\\n### Step 5: Install Hooks\\n\\nIn your test repo, run the `enable` command to install hooks and configure `.factory/settings.json`:\\n\\n```bash\\ncd /tmp/droid-test\\n./entire enable\\n```\\n\\nThis command:\\n- Installs git hooks (prepare-commit-msg, post-commit, pre-push)\\n- Creates `.factory/settings.json` with Entire configuration\\n- Sets up `.entire/logs/` directory\\n\\nVerify the configuration:\\n\\n```bash\\ncat .factory/settings.json\\n```\\n\\n## Running Droid with Local Hooks\\n\\nThis is the critical part. Git hooks invoke `entire` by name (not by absolute path), so they rely on PATH resolution. By default, the system-installed Entire (e.g., `/opt/homebrew/bin/entire`) may be older and won't work correctly with Droid.\\n\\n### Step 1: Prepend Test Repo to PATH\\n\\nBefore launching Droid, ensure your local binary takes precedence:\\n\\n```bash\\ncd /tmp/droid-test\\nexport PATH=\\\"$(pwd):$PATH\\\"\\n```\\n\\nVerify the local binary is found:\\n\\n```bash\\nwhich entire\\n# Should output: /tmp/droid-test/entire\\n```\\n\\n### Step 2: Launch Droid\\n\\n```bash\\ndroid\\n```\\n\\nDroid will detect the `.factory/` directory and begin interacting with Entire through git hooks.\\n\\n## What to Test\\n\\nVerify the following during a Droid session:\\n\\n### Hook Installation\\n\\n```bash\\n# Check that hooks are present\\nls -la .git/hooks/ | grep -E \\\"prepare-commit-msg|post-commit|pre-push\\\"\\n\\n# Verify settings\\ncat .factory/settings.json\\n```\\n\\n### Session Lifecycle\\n\\nAs Droid works, watch for these events in the logs:\\n\\n- **session-start** - New session begins (when Droid starts)\\n- **user-prompt-submit** - Droid submits a prompt\\n- **stop** - Droid stops working on a turn\\n- **session-end** - Session ends (when Droid finishes)\\n\\n### Checkpoints\\n\\nAfter a Droid turn, verify checkpoints were saved:\\n\\n```bash\\n# List checkpoints\\n./entire log\\n\\n# Sample output shows checkpoint IDs, timestamps, and file counts\\n```\\n\\n### Shadow Branches\\n\\nCheck for shadow branches created during the session:\\n\\n```bash\\ngit branch | grep entire/\\n# Should see branches like: entire/<commit-hash>-<worktree-hash>\\n```\\n\\n### Rewind Functionality\\n\\nIf testing rewind, verify you can restore from a checkpoint:\\n\\n```bash\\n# List available rewind points\\n./entire rewind\\n\\n# Rewind to a specific checkpoint (if fully rewinding is supported)\\n./entire rewind <checkpoint-id>\\n```\\n\\n### Commit Condensation\\n\\nWhen Droid makes a commit, verify it includes the Entire-Checkpoint trailer:\\n\\n```bash\\ngit log -1 --format=%B\\n# Should contain: Entire-Checkpoint: <12-hex-char-id>\\n```\\n\\n### Logs\\n\\nAll operations are logged to `.entire/logs/entire.log`. Check for errors or unexpected behavior:\\n\\n```bash\\ncat .entire/logs/entire.log | jq .\\n```\\n\\n## Verifying Hooks Fire\\n\\nWatch hooks execute in real-time using the logs:\\n\\n```bash\\n# Terminal 1: Tail the log with JSON pretty-printing\\ncd /tmp/droid-test\\ntail -f .entire/logs/entire.log | jq .\\n\\n# Terminal 2: Run Droid or make commits\\ndroid\\n# OR\\ncd /tmp/droid-test && git commit -m \\\"test\\\"\\n```\\n\\nFilter logs for Droid-specific activity:\\n\\n```bash\\njq 'select(.msg | test(\\\"factoryai|droid\\\"; \\\"i\\\"))' .entire/logs/entire.log\\n```\\n\\n## Troubleshooting\\n\\n### \\\"Commands called by hooks\\\" Message Appears\\n\\nThis help text indicates the wrong binary is being invoked. The system-installed Entire is handling the hook call instead of your local binary.\\n\\n**Solution:**\\n\\n```bash\\n# Verify PATH is set correctly\\necho $PATH\\nwhich entire  # Should show your test repo path, not /opt/homebrew/bin/entire\\n\\n# Re-export PATH if needed\\nexport PATH=\\\"/tmp/droid-test:$PATH\\\"\\n```\\n\\n### No Logs Appearing\\n\\nIf `.entire/logs/entire.log` is empty or missing, hooks aren't reaching the handler.\\n\\n**Debugging steps:**\\n\\n1. Verify the hooks are executable:\\n   ```bash\\n   ls -la .git/hooks/prepare-commit-msg\\n   chmod +x .git/hooks/prepare-commit-msg\\n   ```\\n\\n2. Test hook execution manually:\\n   ```bash\\n   .git/hooks/prepare-commit-msg /tmp/test-msg\\n   ```\\n\\n3. Check `which entire` resolves to your local binary.\\n\\n### Build Changes Not Reflected\\n\\nIf you modify the CLI code and run Droid with the old binary, you won't see your changes.\\n\\n**Solution:**\\n\\nRebuild the binary after each code change:\\n\\n```bash\\ncd /Users/alisha/Projects/devenv/cli\\ngo build -o /tmp/droid-test/entire ./cmd/entire\\n\\n# Then in test repo, kill Droid and restart\\n```\\n\\n## Alternative: Local-Dev Mode\\n\\nIf you're iterating on code and don't want to rebuild the binary repeatedly, use local-dev mode. This uses `go run` to compile and execute on-the-fly (slower due to compilation, but no rebuild needed).\\n\\n### Setup\\n\\nFrom your test repo:\\n\\n```bash\\ncd /tmp/droid-test\\n\\n# Set the path to the CLI repository\\nREDACTED ./entire enable --local-dev\\n```\\n\\nThis configures Entire to use `go run` instead of a binary, reading code directly from the CLI repository.\\n\\n### Running Droid with Local-Dev\\n\\n```bash\\ncd /tmp/droid-test\\nexport PATH=\\\"$(pwd):$PATH\\\"\\n\\n# Also set the factory project directory for hook execution\\nexport REDACTED\\n\\ndroid\\n```\\n\\nEach hook invocation will compile and run the latest code. This is slower but useful during rapid iteration.\\n\\n### Switching Back to Binary Mode\\n\\nTo revert to binary mode:\\n\\n```bash\\ncd /tmp/droid-test\\n\\n# Rebuild the binary\\ngo build -o /tmp/droid-test/entire /Users/alisha/Projects/devenv/cli/cmd/entire\\n\\n# Re-enable without --local-dev\\n./entire enable\\n```\\n\\n## Cleanup\\n\\nWhen testing is complete, remove the test repository:\\n\\n```bash\\nrm -rf /tmp/droid-test\\n# OR\\nrm -rf ~/Projects/test-repos/factoryai-droid\\n```\\n\\nThis frees up disk space and ensures a clean slate for future tests.\\n\\n## Additional Notes\\n\\n### Session State Management\\n\\nSessions are tracked in `.git/entire-sessions/`. Each active session has a JSON file containing:\\n- Base commit\\n- Checkpoint count\\n- Session phase (ACTIVE, IDLE, ENDED)\\n\\nYou can inspect session state for debugging:\\n\\n```bash\\ncat .git/entire-sessions/*.json | jq .\\n```\\n\\n### Multi-Session Testing\\n\\nIf you want to test multiple concurrent Droid sessions in different worktrees, each worktree gets its own shadow branch namespace (worktree-hash is included in the branch name), so they won't conflict.\\n\\n```bash\\n# In separate worktrees\\ngit worktree add ../test-repo-2\\n\\n# Each worktree can run Droid independently\\n# Shadow branches will be separate: entire/<hash>-<worktree1> and entire/<hash>-<worktree2>\\n```\\n\\n### Git Worktree Considerations\\n\\nThe manual-commit strategy (default) is worktree-aware. Shadow branches include a worktree hash to prevent conflicts when using git worktrees. This allows safe, concurrent Droid sessions across different worktrees in the same repository.\\n\",\"numLines\":345,\"startLine\":1,\"totalLines\":345}},\"sourceToolAssistantUUID\":\"91dc8e31-f196-4e91-bd06-c6b7654478f9\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"01419cb1-416b-4fd0-8cc5-0fa55428236f\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alisha/Projects/devenv/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"9a544f58-48c8-4c6e-b193-59716fe328ea\",\"version\":\"2.1.47\",\"gitBranch\":\"alisha/factoryai-agent\",\"slug\":\"harmonic-mixing-ladybug\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-opus-4-6\",\"id\":\"msg_01P5KUiTeCiFg6o4RtRxjXe1\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Looks good. Note this file is in `test-files/` which is already untracked per your git status. The guide covers everything we ran into, especially the **PATH gotcha** which is the #1 thing to remember.\\n\\nThe key steps in short:\\n\\n1. Create test repo outside CLI project\\n2. `go build -o /path/to/test-repo/entire ./cmd/entire`\\n3. `./entire enable` in the test repo\\n4. **`export PATH=\\\"$(pwd):$PATH\\\"`** before launching `droid` (the critical step)\\n5. Check `.entire/logs/entire.log` to verify hooks are firing\"}],\"stop_reason\":null,\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":1,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":3543,\"cache_read_input