2 — two prompts submitted, but **no `turn-end`/`stop` events** between them\\n- **No phase transitions** logged at all\\n- `session-end` fired **twice** (30ms apart)\\n\\nThe missing `turn-end` events mean no checkpoints were saved. This makes sense — hooks were hitting the old binary (the help text you saw), which returned successfully but did nothing, so Droid never called the `stop` hook handler properly.\\n\\n## Session 2 (`f19b607d`) — Mostly Correct\\n\\nThis is your session after the PATH fix. The lifecycle looks right:\\n\\n```\\nsession-start → turn-start → phase(→active) → turn-end → phase(active→idle) → session-end → phase(idle→ended)\\n```\\n\\n**Three things to note:**\\n\\n1. **`from:\\\"\\\"` on first phase transition** — the initial phase is empty rather than `idle`. This might be expected if the session state machine doesn't set an explicit initial phase, but worth checking if it should default to `idle`.\\n\\n2. **Transcript flush sentinel timeout (WARN)** — this is the 3-second polling that looks for the stop hook sentinel in the transcript. It timed out, meaning the checkpoint may have been saved with an incomplete transcript. Check if Droid writes the sentinel to the JSONL differently than expected.\\n\\n3. **Duplicate `session-end`** — fired twice (40ms apart), same as session 1. This seems like Droid is calling the `SessionEnd` hook twice on exit. Not harmful (second one is a no-op since phase is already `ended`), but worth noting.\\n\\n## Action Items\\n\\n| Issue | Severity | Action |\\n|-------|----------|--------|\\n| Duplicate `session-end` | Low | Likely a Droid behavior — confirm if that's expected on their side |\\n| Transcript flush timeout | Medium | Check if the sentinel format matches what `waitForTranscriptFlush()` expects. Did the checkpoint still save correctly? (`./entire log`) |\\n| Initial phase `from:\\\"\\\"` | Low | Verify if the state machine should initialize to `idle` on `SessionStart` |\\n\\nThe core lifecycle is worki